# JobCheck AI - Project Overview

This document provides a comprehensive summary of the Fake Job Detection (JobCheck AI) project, suitable for creating a presentation (PPT).

## 1. Project Goal & Purpose
**JobCheck AI** is an advanced machine learning platform designed to protect job seekers from employment scams, phishing attempts, and fraudulent postings. It allows users to copy and paste job descriptions and instantly receive a risk assessment score based on NLP analysis and heuristic risk factors.

## 2. Technical Stack
- **Frontend**: Next.js (React), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Framer Motion (for animations), Lucide React (for icons).
- **Backend**: FastAPI (Python), SQLite, PyJWT, bcrypt, uvicorn.
- **Machine Learning**: Scikit-Learn (TF-IDF Vectorizer + Logistic Regression model).

## 3. Architecture Overview

### Frontend (User Interface)
The frontend is built with modern Web design principles:
- **Design System**: Glassmorphism UI, vibrant gradients, abstract AI floating visuals, and dynamic micro-animations.
- **Key Pages**:
  - **Landing Page (`/`)**: Explains the product value, features ("AI Scam Detection", "NLP Analysis"), and interactive transparent UI elements.
  - **Prediction Dashboard (`/predict`)**: A user-friendly interface where users input job descriptions and get a real-time risk gauge (High, Medium, Low risk) outlining flagged words.
  - **History (`/history`)**: Allows logged-in users to review their previously scanned jobs and risk scores.
  - **Authentication**: JWT-based Login and Signup components.

### Backend (API & ML Engine)
The backend is a robust RESTful API powered by FastAPI that serves predictions and handles logic:
- **Core AI Engine**: 
  - Uses [fake_job_model.pkl](file:///c:/Users/My%20PC/Downloads/FakeJobDetection/FakeJobDetection/backend/fake_job_model.pkl) (Logistic Regression) and [vectorizer.pkl](file:///c:/Users/My%20PC/Downloads/FakeJobDetection/FakeJobDetection/backend/vectorizer.pkl) (TF-IDF) trained on a massive dataset ([fake_job_postings.csv](file:///c:/Users/My%20PC/Downloads/FakeJobDetection/FakeJobDetection/backend/fake_job_postings.csv)).
  - **Hybrid Scoring**: Combines ML probabilities with a heuristic rule engine. It penalizes job postings heavily for "High Risk" patterns (e.g., "registration fee", "wire transfer") and promotes "Real Keywords" (e.g., "benefits", "responsibilities").
- **Authentication**: Uses `bcrypt` for password hashing and `jose` for secure JWT generation.
- **Database**: SQLite tracking `user`, `jobpostsubmission`, `predictionresult`, and `flaggedpost`.
- **Admin Features**: Includes `/admin/stats`, `/admin/daily-stats`, `/admin/export-pdf`, and `/admin/export-csv` endpoints to observe metrics and download analysis reports (via `fpdf` and [csv](file:///c:/Users/My%20PC/Downloads/FakeJobDetection/FakeJobDetection/backend/fake_job_postings.csv) modules). It also supports real-time model retraining (`/admin/retrain`).

## 4. Key Features & Selling Points (For PPT Slides)
- **Real-Time Analysis**: Instantaneous evaluations under 1 second.
- **Transparent Scoring**: Highlights exactly *why* a job was flagged (e.g. highlights "urgent hiring" or "whatsapp").
- **Career Protection**: Helps applicants avoid identity theft and financial scams.
- **Personal Log (History)**: Users can track suspect listings over time.
- **Continuous Learning**: Admin endpoints exist to retrain the ML model dynamically with new data.

## 5. Security & Privacy
- Accounts are protected using JWT tokens.
- Passwords are securely hashed.
- Role-based views (Admin vs Standard User).

